How to run the application 

1. Python 2.7 require
	i)  install python from https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-279/
	ii) After the installation is complete double check to make sure you see python in your PATH. 
		You can find your path by opening your control panel -> System and Security -> System -> Advanced System Settings -> Environment 
		Variables -> Selecting Path -> Edit ->

		Now youâ€™re looking at your Path. Be Careful, if you delete or add to the path accidently you may break other programs.
		You need to confirm that C:\Python27; and C:\Python27\Scripts; is part of your path.
	
2) Install pip 
	Use this stackoverflow post to install pip https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4750806/how-do-i-install-pip-on-windows

3) Install virtualenv
	pip install virtualenv
	
4) Install virtualenvwrapper-win
	pip to install virtualenvwrapper-win
	
5) Create the project directory
	and using cmd go to the directory and install flask 
		pip install flask
		
6) Install all other pacakeges
	i) 	pip install flask-wtf
	ii) pip install flask-sqlalchemy
	iii)pip install flask_bcrypt
	iv)	pip install mysql-connector
	v)	pip install flask-mysql
	vi) pip install flask-MySqldb
	
7) Set Virtual Environment
	set FLASK_APP = app.py
	
8) Running the flask app
	Run flask
	

